Again, left with nothing to do. Wound up at a table by myself in the back of the room, reading random whatevers from the class shelves. According to the metrics the NTs devised, I didn’t need accommodation under disability law, because look at my grades. Such. BULLSHIT.

Reading lessons were a big part of the day. And I’d read the books. So what was left? Twiddling, fidgeting, playing with things. Fighting boredom. The same happened in second grade only it wasn’t just the reading workbooks it was all of our textbook.

When I started kindergarten I sat down in the reading cubby during lunch break and read the year’s workbooks. All of them. Not to show off, but just because I liked to read, and I COULD read, so I DID. This left me without anything to do the rest of the year.
